  • Method Details

    • bubbleSort

      public static <T extends Comparable<Shape>> void bubbleSort(Shape[] shapes)
      This method processes through a Bubble Sort. It takes an array of shapes, and compares each element with the one next to it. If the latter height is bigger, they switch positions. A single iteration will place the smallest item in the last position of the array. Then, we need to keep iterating to place the smallest unsorted element at the end of the unsorted portion of the array.
      Parameters:
      shapes - represents a list of shapes being passed into the method

    • bubbleSort

      public static void bubbleSort(Shape[] shapes, Comparator<Shape> c)
      This method processes through a Bubble Sort. It takes an array of shapes, and compares each element with the one next to it. If the latter comparison factor is bigger, they switch positions. A single iteration will place the smallest item in the last position of the array. Then, we need to keep iterating to place the smallest unsorted element at the end of the unsorted portion of the array.
      Parameters:
      shapes - represents a list of shapes being passed into the method
      c - represents the compare type to be used for the sorting

    • selectionSort

      public static void selectionSort(Shape[] shapes)
      This method processes through a Selection Sort. It takes an array of shapes, and finds the item with the biggest height value. We iterate through the array scanning for an element with a bigger height, and switches them when found. Therefore, after each iteration the biggest value from the unsorted portion of the array is placed in the last index of the sorted portion.
      Parameters:
      shapes - represents a list of shapes being passed into the method

    • selectionSort

      public static void selectionSort(Shape[] shapes, Comparator<Shape> c)
      This method processes through a Selection Sort. It takes an array of shapes, and finds the item with the biggest value for the comparator factor. We iterate through the array scanning for an element with a bigger value, and switches them when found. Therefore, after each iteration the biggest value from the unsorted portion of the array is placed in the last index of the sorted portion.
      Parameters:
      shapes - represents a list of shapes being passed into the method
      c - represents the compare type to be used for the sorting

    • insertionSort

      public static void insertionSort(Shape[] array)
      This method processes through an Insertion Sort. It takes an array of shapes, and compares each element with the one before it. If the latter height is bigger, they switch positions. This process is repeated until the array is sorted.
      Parameters:
      shapes - represents a list of shapes being passed into the method

    • mergeSort

      public static void mergeSort(Shape[] shapes)
      This method processes through a Merge Sort. It takes an array of shapes, breaks them down into smaller arrays until each contains only one element. Then, it merges pair of arrays while ordering its elements.
      Parameters:
      shapes - represents a list of shapes being passed into the method

    • quickSort

      public static void quickSort(Shape[] shapes)
      This method processes through a Quick Sort. It takes an array of shapes, and chooses the last element as the pivot. It then compares each element with the pivot, and if the element is bigger, it is placed to the right of the pivot. The process is repeated until the array is sorted.
      Parameters:
      shapes - represents a list of shapes being passed into the method
